AN ACT relating to governmental administration; revising the membership of the
Nevada State Board on Geographic Names; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Nevada State Board on Geographic Names to coordinate and
2 approve geographic names within the State for official recommendation to the United States
3 Board on Geographic Names. (NRS 327.110) The Nevada State Board on Geographic Names
4 consists of 12 voting members, which include various representatives from various state and
5 federal agencies and the Inter-Tribal Council of Nevada, Inc. (NRS 327.120) Section 1 of this
6 bill: (1) removes the [representatives] representative from [both the United States National
7 Park Service and] the Nevada Historical Society on the Nevada State Board on Geographic
8 Names; [and] (2) adds to the Board one representative [each] from the Division of Museums
9 and History of the Department of Tourism and Cultural Affairs [and the United States Fish
10 and Wildlife Service.] ; (3) clarifies that the representative from the Department of Native
11 American Affairs is from the Department of Native American Affairs of this State; and
12 (4) changes the representatives from the United States Bureau of Land Management, the
13 United States Forest Service and the United States National Park Service from voting
14 members of the Board to nonvoting members. Section 2 of this bill allows the
15 [representatives] representative appointed by [the United States National Park Service and]
16 the Nevada Historical Society who [are] is serving on the Board on or before July 1, 2025, to
17 continue serving on the Board until [their successors are] the representative’s successor is
18 designated by the appropriate [agencies] agency in accordance with the provisions of section
19 1.
